<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Session_SaveHandler_DbTable cannot save objects serialized with the PHP serialize() function.</p>

<p>If I take the following class:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class Foo {
    protected $_bar;
}
</code></pre>

<p>serialize it using the serialize() function and store it in a Session Namespace, I will be presented with a fatal exception.</p>

<p>The exception appears as such:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Fatal error: Exception thrown without a stack frame in Unknown on line 0
</code></pre>

<p>When I check my database I find that no row has been created. The PHP docs mention you should try base64 encoding the serialized data, but I'm unsure whether this is a bug at this stage.
I have tested this on a Windows 2003 Server running IIS 6.0, MSSQL 2005 and PHP 5.2.5.</p>

